events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Indiana Pacers

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam had 24 points and 11 rebounds, Tyrese Haliburton added 17 points and 13 assists — four on late consecutive possessions — and the Indiana Pacers beat the New Orleans Pelicans 123-114 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacers beat Pelicans 123-114 to open home-and-home set

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 30 points, 16 assists and 11 rebounds on his 25th birthday for his 11th triple-double of the season, Kyrie Irving scored 15 of his 29 points in the fourth quarter and the Dallas Mavericks beat the Toronto Raptors 136-125 on Wednesday...
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic gets 11th triple-double of season on 25th birthday as Mavericks beat Raptors 136-125

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 17 of his 34 points in the third quarter, helping the Minnesota Timberwolves move into sole possession of first place in the Western Conference with a 110-101 win over the Memphis Grizzlies on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony Edwards scores 34, Timberwolves move into 1st in West with 110-101 win over Grizzlies

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan made the big shots down the stretch and Andre Drummond dominated on the glass. It was just enough to lift the Chicago Bulls past one of the Eastern Conference's best teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeMar DeRozan scores 35 points, Bulls outlast Cavaliers 132-123 in 2OT

headlines.description: — Jamal Murray scored 32 points, Nikola Jokic had 14 points, 14 rebounds and 11 assists in just three quarters for his fourth straight triple-double and the Denver Nuggets had a big run to beat the short-handed Sacramento Kings 117-96 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jamal Murray scores 32 points, Nuggets use big run to beat Kings 117-96

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at LA Clippers

headlines.description: - LeBron James scored 19 of his 34 points during a brilliant fourth quarter, leading the Los Angeles Lakers back from a 21-point deficit for a dramatic 116-112 victory over the Los Angeles Clippers on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron scores 34 points, leads Lakers' rally from 21-point deficit in 116-112 win over Clippers
